Repository state handoff - 2026-05-12

Completed slice:
- Added Chumsky 0.13.0-based lexer foundation in `linguini-syntax`, including token/span model, lexer recovery, schema-specific lexing, and committed token snapshots.
- Added schema parser AST and `parse_schema` entry point for enums, custom scalar aliases, schema formatter annotations, message signatures, grouped messages, and doc comments.
- Added locale parser AST and `parse_locale` entry point for local enums, forms, selector maps, plural-map-shaped branches, local functions, public/grouped message implementations, placeholders, dotted/call expressions, and placeholder formatter annotations.
- Added recursive nested form attribute parsing for object-shaped attributes inside locale forms.
- Added parser recovery entry points for schema and locale parsing. They return `ParseOutput<T>` with optional AST plus collected lex and parse diagnostics.
- Added invalid schema and locale fixtures that assert diagnostics are produced while strict parser APIs still fail.
- Expanded golden schema and Russian locale fixtures from minimal examples to spec-shaped fixtures covering docs, formatter annotations, forms, selector maps, plural-shaped maps, nested form attributes, helper functions, placeholders, and grouped messages.
- Updated parser and fixture checklist items through parser recovery and invalid fixture diagnostics.

Implementation decisions:
- Lexer uses `chumsky = "0.13.0"`.
- Public spans are byte offsets.
- Raw text after `=` and `=>` currently includes leading spaces, matching "text after delimiter" literally.
- `lex_schema` disables raw-text transition after `=` because schema custom scalar aliases use code syntax after equals.
- Mode transitions are coordinated in Rust, while token recognition is done with Chumsky parsers.
- `TokenKind::Error` represents recovered invalid source characters.
- Placeholder mode tokenizes code punctuation without letting `=` switch into raw text.
- Multiline raw text currently treats `"` as a delimiter boundary so triple quotes can be recognized; escaped/ordinary quotes in raw text are deferred.
- Parser trivia stripping removes whitespace, newlines, and ordinary comments, but preserves doc comments as AST nodes.
- Recovered parser APIs use recovered lexing, drop `TokenKind::Error` tokens, then preserve all lex and parse errors in order.
- Schema parser is syntax-only and does not resolve type names or formatter semantics.
- Locale parser is syntax-only and does not resolve schema messages, form variants, selector enums, CLDR plural categories, formatter compatibility, or function arity.
- Locale `name = value` attributes are parsed as text patterns because the lexer intentionally enters raw-text mode after `=`; scalar-vs-text meaning is deferred to semantic analysis.
- Form map bodies cover branch maps used by selector and plural-shaped examples, and recursive object-shaped nested attributes used by forms.

